1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3 O-O 9. d3 Bg4 $2 {With no central tension involving the squares d4 and e5, this is an absolutely pointless move. White should now happily accept the invitation to win time on the bishop and start a quick kingside initiative.} 10. h3 Bh5 11. Nbd2 Na5 12. Bc2 c5 13. Nf1 Re8 14. Ng3 Bg6 15. Nh4 $16 *

