1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. e5 d5 6. Bb5 Nd7 7. O-O Be7 8. Re1 O-O 9. Bxc6 bxc6 10. Nxd4 Nb8 11. f4 c5 12. Nf3 Nc6 $17 13. Nc3 (13. c4 {This is an important move to consider.} dxc4 {Don't reject this move because it damages the pawn structure. Black's light-squared bishop is very strong and all squares on the d-file are weak for White, so this move should be considered.} (13... d4 {This is a good move since it's difficult for White to establish a blockade with a knight on the d3-square, and even if that happens, it will be under constant pressure from a bishop on f5 and potentially the knight coming to the b4-square.}) 14. Nc3 Bf5 15. Be3 Nb4 {The knight is heading to the d3-square.} (15... Bd3 {Placing the bishop on d3 is also possible.})) 13... d4 14. Ne4 Be6 15. Ng3 Qd7 {Preventing f4-f5.} 16. c3 Rad8 17. Qa4 Bd5 18. f5 Bxf3 19. gxf3 Qd5 20. f6 gxf6 21. Nf5 Qxf3 22. Rf1 Qg4+ 23. Kh1 Qe4+ 24. Kg1 Kh8 25. Ng3 Rg8 26. Bf4 fxe5 27. Rae1 Qd5 28. c4 Qe6 29. Bd2 Bh4 30. Rf3 e4 31. Qc2 Ne5 32. Ra3 d3 33. Qd1 Bxg3 34. hxg3 Rxg3+ 35. Kf2 Rdg8 36. Rxe4 Rg2+ 37. Ke3 R8g3+ 0-1

