1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. e5 d5 6. Bb5 Nd7 7. O-O Be7 8. Bxc6 bxc6 9. Nxd4 Nb8 10. Qf3 c5 $1 11. Nb5 {White is threatening Qxd5.} O-O 12. c4 $1 (12. Bf4 $2 {A slow type of move such as this one, gives Black enough time to consolidate and claim an advantage.} Be6 13. Nd2 Nc6 $17 {Black can push away White's knight on b5 with a7-a6.} 14. Na3 Nd4 15. Qd1 f6 16. c3 Nc6 17. exf6 Rxf6 18. Bg5 Rg6 19. Bxe7 Qxe7 20. Re1 Qg5 21. g3 Rf8 22. Nf3 Qf6 23. Re3 d4 24. cxd4 cxd4 25. Rd3 Bd5 26. Nb5 Bxf3 27. Qb3+ Kh8 28. Rd2 Be4 29. Re1 Ne5 30. Nxd4 Qh4 31. Qe3 Ng4 32. Nf3 Rxf3 33. Qxf3 Qxh2+ 34. Kf1 Qh3+ 35. Kg1 Qh2+ 36. Kf1 Qh3+ 37. Kg1 Qh2+) 12... c6 $1 (12... Ba6 $5 $36 {This move can also be considered.}) 13. cxd5 (13. Nd6 $2 Be6 {Remember this idea. Black allowed White to place the knight on the d6-square, but now, the knight is vulnerable since Black has ideas like Nd7-Nxe5.} 14. Nf5 Bxf5 15. Qxf5 Qd7 $17) 13... cxd5 14. Rd1 Be6 15. N1c3 $1 (15. N5c3 $4 Nc6 16. Nxd5 (16. Be3 Nxe5 17. Qg3 Ng6 18. Nxd5 Bxd5 19. Nc3 Bd6 20. Qh3 Bc6 $19) 16... Nd4 17. Nxe7+ Qxe7 $19 18. Qe4 Bf5 $19 {[%csl Ra1][%cal Gd4c2,Gc2a1]}) 15... Qd7 16. Qg3 $1 (16. Nd6 Nc6 17. Nxd5 $2 Bg4 $19) (16. Nxd5 $4 Bxd5 17. Qxd5 Qxb5 18. Qxa8 Nc6 $19) 16... d4 17. Bh6 Bg4 18. Nc7 (18. e6 Qxe6 $17) 18... Qxc7 19. Qxg4 Qxe5 20. Re1 Qf6 21. Nd5 Qxh6 22. Nxe7+ Kh8 23. b4 cxb4 24. Qxd4 Nc6 25. Nxc6 Qxc6 26. Qxb4 $11 1/2-1/2

