1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. e5 d5 6. Bb5 Nd7 7. O-O Be7 8. c3 (8. Bf4 {A good thing about the line that's recommended against the Scotch Gambit is that White doesn't have many possibilities to get creative and find novelties since Black's play is straightforward.} O-O 9. Bxc6 bxc6 10. Nxd4 Nb8 11. Nc3 c5 12. Nf3 Be6 {Black has the advantage and a very comfortable position.}) 8... dxc3 9. Nxc3 a6 (9... Nb6 {This is also fine for Black.} 10. Nd4 $6 Bd7 11. e6 fxe6 12. Bxc6 bxc6 13. Qh5+ g6 14. Qh6 (14. Qe5 Bf6 $19) 14... Bf8 15. Qh3 Qf6 $19) 10. Bxc6 bxc6 11. e6 fxe6 12. Nd4 Nb8 $17 13. Qh5+ (13. Re1 O-O {Black should always be ready to give one pawn back in order to take over the initiative.} 14. Nxe6 Bxe6 15. Rxe6 Bd6 16. Qg4 Nd7 17. Bh6 Rf7 $19) 13... g6 14. Qe2 Qd6 15. Bh6 e5 16. Nb3 Bf8 17. Be3 Bg7 18. Bc5 Qe6 19. Rfe1 Nd7 20. Nd4 Qf6 21. Ba3 Bf8 (21... Bb7 22. Rad1 O-O-O $17) 22. f4 e4 23. Nxe4 Qxd4+ 24. Nf2+ Kf7 25. Rad1 Qc4 26. Qe8+ Kg7 27. Re7+ Bxe7 28. Qxe7+ Kh6 29. Ng4+ 1-0

