1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 Nf6 5. e5 d5 6. Bb5 Nd7 7. O-O Be7 8. Bxc6 bxc6 9. Nxd4 Nb8 10. Qf3 O-O 11. Nf5 (11. Re1 {White doesn't put any pressure on Black's center and allows:} c5 12. Nf5 {The following sequence is a very typical idea of how to meet the Nf5 move.} Bxf5 13. Qxf5 Qd7 {Remember this idea! Black is taking over now.} 14. Qxd7 (14. Qf3 Nc6 $15) 14... Nxd7 15. Nc3 c6 $15) 11... Bxf5 12. Qxf5 Qd7 $15 13. Qd3 Qe6 14. Bf4 (14. f4 f6 {Black is trying to open up the position as quickly as possible.} (14... Nd7 $15 {Is also possible in this position.}) 15. exf6 Bxf6 $17) 14... Nd7 15. Qg3 f6 16. exf6 Nxf6 17. Qd3 Ne4 18. Be3 c5 19. Nc3 Nxc3 20. bxc3 c4 21. Qd2 c5 22. Rae1 Qf5 23. Bd4 Rfe8 24. Be5 Rad8 25. Bc7 Rd7 26. Bg3 Red8 27. Rxe7 Rxe7 28. Bh4 Red7 29. Bxd8 Rxd8 30. Qe2 Qe4 31. Qxe4 dxe4 32. Rc1 Rd2 33. Kf1 Kf7 34. Rb1 Rxc2 35. Rb5 Rxc3 36. Rxc5 Rc2 37. h4 Ke6 38. h5 Kd6 39. Rc8 c3 40. Ke1 e3 41. fxe3 Rxg2 42. Rxc3 Rxa2 43. Rc4 Rb2 44. Rd4+ Ke6 45. Ra4 Rb7 46. Ra5 Kd6 47. Kd2 Kc6 48. Kc3 Kb6 49. Re5 Rc7+ 50. Kb4 Kc6 51. Ra5 Kd6 52. Rg5 Ke6 53. e4 Kf7 54. Rf5+ Kg8 55. Rg5 Re7 56. e5 Kf7 57. Kc5 Ke6 58. Kd4 a5 59. Kc4 a4 60. Kb4 Ra7 61. Ka3 h6 62. Rg6+ Kxe5 63. Ka2 a3 64. Ka1 a2 65. Rb6 Ke4 66. Rg6 Kf5 67. Rg2 Kf6 68. Rg6+ Kf7 69. Rg2 Ra5 70. Rf2+ Kg8 71. Rh2 Kh7 72. Rh3 g6 73. hxg6+ Kxg6 74. Rg3+ Kf5 75. Rh3 Kg5 76. Rg3+ Kf4 77. Rh3 h5 78. Rh4+ Kg5 79. Rc4 h4 80. Rc3 Ra4 81. Rb3 Kg4 82. Rc3 h3 0-1

