1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 Nf6 5. e5 d5 6. Bb5 Nd7 7. O-O Be7 8. Bxc6 bxc6 9. Nxd4 Nb8 10. f4 {Black needs to be a bit careful now since castling would allow f4-f5, so playing in the center first is good.} c5 11. Nf3 h5 (11... Nc6 {I would prefer this move over 11...h5, although that move is also possible.}) 12. c3 c6 13. Be3 Bf5 14. Nbd2 a5 {Discouraging any b2-b4 ideas that White may have.} 15. b3 Nd7 16. Ne1 Nf8 $17 17. Ndf3 Ne6 {Black established a very nice blockade and has a big advantage.} 18. Qd2 O-O 19. g3 a4 20. Ng2 Be4 21. Qe2 g6 22. Nfh4 axb3 23. axb3 Rxa1 24. Rxa1 Ng7 25. Qf2 Qb6 26. b4 d4 27. cxd4 cxd4 28. Bxd4 Qxb4 29. Rc1 Rd8 30. Be3 c5 31. Qe1 Ne6 32. h3 Qxe1+ 33. Nxe1 Bxh4 34. gxh4 Rc8 35. Kf2 c4 36. Rc3 Ng7 37. Nf3 Nf5 38. Nd4 Nxh4 39. Nb5 Bd5 40. Nd6 Rb8 41. Kg3 Ng2 42. Nxc4 h4+ 43. Kf2 Rb4 44. Bd2 Kh7 45. Rc1 Rb3 46. Nd6 Rb2 47. Ke2 Nxf4+ 48. Ke3 g5 49. Ne8 Kg6 50. Nf6 Be6 51. Ne4 Rb3+ 52. Kf2 Nd3+ 53. Ke2 Nxc1+ 54. Bxc1 Bd5 55. Nxg5 Rc3 56. Bd2 Rc2 57. Kd3 Rxd2+ 58. Kxd2 Kxg5 0-1

