1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 Nf6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. O-O Nxe4 {As a general rule for any Nc3 gambits: Black captures on c3 with the knight when it's possible, and when it isn't possible, Black captures with the pawn.} 6. Re1 (6. Nc3 Nxc3 {Capturing with the pawn leads to a lot of complications, so capturing with the knight on c3 is simple and good.} 7. bxc3 d5 8. Bb5 Be7 {Black doesn't have enough time to keep both extra pawns since the king will be stuck in the center, instead, Black tries to finish the development and stay with one extra pawn.} 9. Ne5 (9. Nxd4 Bd7 $17) 9... Bd7 10. Bxc6 Bxc6 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. cxd4 O-O $17 13. c4 $6 dxc4 {Black has a material advantage and will put pressure on White's d4-pawn.}) 6... d5 7. Bxd5 (7. Nc3 dxc3 8. Bxd5 Be6 9. Bxe4 (9. Rxe4 $4 Ne7 $19) 9... Qxd1 10. Rxd1 cxb2 11. Bxb2 f6 {Limits the scope of White's dark-squared bishop.} 12. Bxc6+ bxc6 13. Nd4 Bd7 14. f3 Bd6 $17) 7... Qxd5 8. Nc3 Qd7 9. Nxe4 Be7 10. Bg5 O-O 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 12. Nxd4 Bd7 (12... Nxd4 {Capturing on d4 is also possible, although 12...Bd7 is more accurate.} 13. Qxd4 b6 {Black's idea is to play Be6 without allowing the move Nc5.}) 13. Nb3 Rae8 {13...Rad8 is also possible.} 14. Qd2 (14. Nec5 Qxe1+ 15. Qxe1 Rxe1+ 16. Rxe1 Bc8 $15) 14... Bc8 15. Nc3 Qf6 16. Rxe8 Rxe8 17. Re1 Rd8 (17... Rxe1+ 18. Qxe1 Qd8 $15 (18... Kf8 $1 {This is the best move according to the engine where Black has a comfortable advantage.})) 18. Qe3 h6 19. h3 Bf5 20. Re2 Qg6 21. Ne4 Rd1+ 22. Kh2 Rb1 23. Ng3 Rxb2 24. Nd4 Bd7 25. Qf4 Qd6 26. Qxd6 cxd6 27. Ndf5 Rxa2 28. Nxd6 Rb2 29. Nge4 b6 30. Nc4 Rb4 31. Ned6 Be6 32. Ne5 Nxe5 33. Rxe5 a5 34. Rb5 Rxb5 35. Nxb5 Kf8 36. Kg3 Ke7 37. Kf4 Bc4 38. Na3 Bf1 39. g3 b5 40. c3 b4 41. cxb4 axb4 42. Nc2 b3 43. Na3 Bxh3 44. Ke5 Be6 45. Kd4 g5 46. Kc3 h5 47. Nb5 h4 48. Nd4 h3 49. Nf3 g4 50. Nh2 f5 51. Kb2 Kd6 52. Kc3 Kc5 53. Nf1 Kb5 54. Nh2 Ka4 55. Kb2 Kb4 56. f3 Kc4 57. fxg4 fxg4 58. Nf1 Kd3 0-1

