1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 Nf6 5. O-O Nxe4 6. Re1 d5 7. Bxd5 Qxd5 8. Nc3 Qd7 9. Rxe4+ Be7 10. Nxd4 f5 {This is a move that you need to remember if White captures with the rook on e4 on move 9.} 11. Rf4 O-O 12. Nxc6 Qxc6 13. Qd5+ Qe6 (13... Qxd5 {It's slightly more accurate to capture the queen on d5.} 14. Nxd5 Bd8 $1 {Not Bd6 as Black doesn't want to oppose the bishop that will come on f4 soon (after Rd4 and Bf4 for example), instead, Black would like to keep the bishop pair.} 15. Rd4 c6 16. Nc3 Bf6 17. Rd1 Be6 {With a very comfortable advantage for Black.}) 14. Rf3 c6 15. Qxe6+ Bxe6 16. Bf4 Kf7 17. Be5 Rad8 18. Re1 g6 19. Rd3 Rxd3 20. cxd3 Rd8 21. Rd1 b5 22. b3 a5 23. Ne2 a4 24. Nd4 Bd5 25. Rc1 axb3 26. axb3 b4 27. Rb1 c5 28. Ne2 Bc6 29. Rd1 Bb5 30. Nc1 c4 31. bxc4 Bxc4 32. Kf1 b3 33. Bb2 Bb4 34. f3 g5 35. Kf2 Bd5 36. Ne2 Ra8 37. Nc3 Bxc3 38. Bxc3 Ra2+ 39. Bd2 Rc2 0-1

