{[%evp 0,7,33,33,47,47,47,9,9,-29] The main focus of this lecture is the position arising after} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. Ng5 {This system is objectively fine but very impractical for White. The reason is that Black will sacrifice a pawn in order to overtake the initiative. In the arising positions, Black's play is easier from human perspective. The main line goes:} d5 5. exd5 Na5 6. Bb5+ c6 7. dxc6 bxc6 {In this position, the modern main line starts with} 8. Bd3 {Obviously, I examine all the alternatives. Black has an easy play in all the directions.} *

