1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. Ng5 d5 5. exd5 Na5 6. Bb5+ c6 7. dxc6 bxc6 8. Bd3 Nd5 9. h4 g6 10. O-O ({Possibly} 10. Nc3 {is the best move} Rb8 {This is interesting stopping b4} (10... h6 {Is also interesting and unclear.} 11. Nxd5 cxd5 12. Bb5+ Bd7 13. Bxd7+ Qxd7 14. Nf3 Bg7 15. d4 f6 {Controlling the e5-square. A very nice and educative move intending to play e4 on the next move.} 16. dxe5 fxe5 17. O-O O-O {With good compensation.})) 10... Bg7 11. Be2 h6 12. Ne4 f5 13. Ng3 Qxh4 {Now Black should be much better and won after a few moves.} 14. Nc3 O-O {White has very difficult moves to make that only the computer can make.} 15. d3 Rb8 16. Bf3 Be6 17. Bd2 Nb7 18. Rb1 Nc5 19. Re1 Kh7 20. b4 Nxb4 21. a3 Nd5 22. Nxd5 cxd5 23. Bb4 Rfc8 24. d4 Ne4 25. Bxe4 dxe4 26. d5 Bd7 27. Bd6 Rxb1 28. Qxb1 Qf6 29. Bb4 Qb6 30. Qb3 a5 31. Be7 Qxb3 32. cxb3 Kg8 33. b4 Kf7 34. Bc5 axb4 35. axb4 Ra8 36. Ne2 Ra2 37. Nc3 Rc2 38. Nb1 h5 39. Rd1 Bh6 40. Na3 Rc3 41. Ra1 h4 42. Bd6 Kf6 43. b5 e3 44. b6 exf2+ 45. Kf1 Rb3 46. Rb1 Rxb1+ 47. Nxb1 Be3 48. Na3 Bxb6 49. Bxe5+ Kg5 50. Bd6 Kg4 51. Bb4 f4 52. Bd6 Bf5 0-1

