1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. Ng5 d5 5. exd5 Na5 6. Bb5+ c6 7. dxc6 bxc6 8. Bd3 Nd5 9. Nf3 Bd6 ({I even tried} 9... g5 {but it is not good at all.} 10. Nxe5 (10. O-O Bg7 11. Re1 f6 12. Bf1 O-O 13. d4) 10... Bg7) 10. O-O O-O (10... f5 11. Re1 (11. Nxe5 O-O (11... Bxe5 12. Re1 Qe7 13. Qe2) 12. Re1 Qf6 13. Nf3) 11... e4) 11. Re1 Re8 {The more quiet move. Maybe that is the move you want to make.} 12. Nc3 ({After} 12. Bf1 {Black will play} e4 {before White stabilizes with d3.}) 12... f5 13. Bf1 e4 {Even though it appears to be tremendous for Black, it is not so clear I would say.} (13... h6 14. d4 e4 15. Ne5) (13... Rb8 14. d4) 14. Nxd5 cxd5 (14... exf3 15. Rxe8+ Qxe8 16. Nc3 fxg2 17. Bxg2) 15. Nd4 {Strangely enough, the computer tends to give White an advantage.} Be5 $5 (15... Qf6 16. c3 Bb7 17. d3 (17. b4 Nc6) 17... f4 (17... Rad8)) (15... Qh4 16. g3 Qf6 17. c3 f4 18. d3 Rf8 19. Qc2 e3 20. Bxe3 fxe3 21. Rxe3 Bg4 22. Bg2 Kh8 23. h3 Bd7 24. Rae1 Rac8 25. Ne6 Rfe8 26. Qe2 Bc6 27. b4 Nb7 28. Nd4 Rxe3 29. Qxe3 Bf8 30. Qf3 Nd8 31. Nxc6 Nxc6 32. Qxf6 gxf6 33. Bxd5 Ne5 34. d4 Nd3 35. Re6 Rxc3 36. b5 Kg7 37. a4 Nb4 38. Be4 Rc4 39. d5 Rd4 40. a5 Bc5 41. d6 Bxd6 42. b6 axb6 43. axb6 Kf7 44. Bf5 Nc6 45. b7 Nb8 46. Re2 h6 47. Kg2 Rb4 48. Be4 Nd7 49. Bd5+ Kf8 50. Re6 Rb6 51. h4 Bb8 52. Rxb6 Nxb6 53. Be4 Ke7 54. Kf3 Nc4 55. Kg4 Nd6 56. Bd5 Kf8 57. Kh5 Kg7 58. g4 Nb5 59. Be4 Nd6 60. Bd5 f5 61. gxf5 Ne8 62. Kg4 Nf6+ 63. Kf3 Nxd5 64. Ke4 Ne7) 16. c3 Qd6 {All these are acceptable moves.} 17. h3 {The general characteristics remain.} (17. Qa4 Bxh2+ 18. Kh1 Bb7 (18... Rf8 $1 19. d3 (19. Qxa5 Qh6 20. Qxd5+ Kh8 21. Bc4 Rb8 22. d3 f4 $19) 19... Nb7 20. Qc6 Be5 21. Qxd6 Nxd6 22. dxe4 fxe4) 19. d3 (19. Qxa5 $4 Qh6 20. Nxf5 Qh5) 19... Nc6) (17. Qh5 $2 g6 18. Qh3 Qd8 (18... f4) 19. d3 f4 20. Qh6 Rf8 21. dxe4 Bg7) 17... Nc6 18. Nxc6 Qxc6 19. d3 (19. d4 Bc7 $36) 19... Rb8 20. a4 (20. dxe4 fxe4 21. Rb1 (21. Qc2 d4) 21... Rb7 22. Be3 Rf8) 20... Rf8 {With compensation for the pawn and finally Black won in the end.} 0-1

