1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. Ng5 d5 5. exd5 Na5 6. Bb5+ c6 7. dxc6 bxc6 8. Bd3 Nd5 9. Nf3 Bd6 10. O-O Nf4 11. Re1 Nxd3 12. cxd3 O-O 13. Nc3 c5 14. b3 f6 {I am not even sure if that is a good move. But it appears to be interesting.} 15. Ne4 Be7 16. Ba3 Nb7 {That was the idea and is why Black did not play Nc6 so early. He wants to defend his own pawns and win back the d3-pawn.} 17. Qc2 Qa5 {With tempo.} 18. Qc4+ Kh8 19. Bb2 Qb6 {A simple solution intending Be6 proving Black with good compensation.} 20. Rac1 Be6 21. Qc3 Qa6 {There was a sacrifice.} 22. Nxe5 fxe5 23. Qxe5 Rf7 24. Re3 Bf5 {and Black won in the end.} 25. Rce1 Bxe4 26. Qxe4 Bf8 27. Rh3 h6 28. Qd5 Kg8 29. Rf3 Qg6 30. Re6 Rd8 31. Qc4 Na5 32. Rxg6 Nxc4 33. bxc4 Rb8 34. Rxf7 Kxf7 35. Ra6 Rxb2 36. Rxa7+ Be7 37. g4 Rxd2 38. Rd7 Rxa2 39. Rd5 Bh4 40. f4 Bf6 41. Kh1 Bd4 42. h4 Rd2 43. h5 Rxd3 44. Kg2 Rc3 45. g5 Rxc4 46. Kf3 Rc3+ 47. Kg4 Ke6 48. Rd8 Rc1 49. gxh6 Rg1+ 50. Kf3 gxh6 51. Ra8 Kf5 52. Rf8+ Bf6 53. Rc8 Rc1 54. Rc6 Rc3+ 55. Ke2 c4 56. Kd2 Rd3+ 57. Ke2 Rd4 58. Ke3 Re4+ 0-1

