{This is an online 10 minutes game.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. Ng5 d5 5. exd5 Na5 6. Bb5+ c6 7. dxc6 bxc6 8. Be2 h6 9. Nf3 e4 10. Ne5 Bc5 11. c3 Bd6 ({I should have played} 11... Qc7 $1 {The difference is that after} 12. f4 (12. d4 exd3 13. Nxd3 Bd6) 12... Bb6 {The bishop would stay on the long diagonal.}) 12. f4 {My opponent surprised me with this move.} O-O (12... exf3 {is also quite interesting and possibly the best.} 13. Nxf3 Ng4 {with nice compensation.}) 13. O-O c5 {There is compensation. f4 gives Black attacking possibilities.} 14. d4 exd3 15. Bxd3 c4 16. Bc2 {There is a big problem with my position: the knight on a5.} ({He should not capture the pawn as he will be checkmated very easily.} 16. Nxc4 Nxc4 17. Bxc4 Bc5+ 18. Kh1 Qxd1 19. Rxd1 Ng4 {The knight is coming to f2.} 20. Rf1 Re8) 16... Qb6+ 17. Kh1 Bb7 18. Qe2 Bc5 19. Nd2 Rfe8 20. b4 {A very strong move.} cxb3 21. axb3 Ba6 {Forcing him to play c4 as he was threatening b4.} 22. c4 Bb7 23. Bb2 Rad8 {I put the pieces in the center.} 24. Bc3 Nc6 25. Ndf3 Ng4 26. Qe4 Nf6 27. Qe2 {According to the computer, we played quite well up to a point and the position is 0.00.} Ng4 {Maybe threatening some Nf2 or Ne3 ideas.} 28. Qe4 Nf6 ({I did not like to play} 28... g6 29. Nxg4 Rxe4 30. Nf6+ {because this can become very annoying in blitz games.}) 29. Qe2 {Draw by Repetition} 1/2-1/2

