1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d3 h6 5. O-O d6 6. c3 g6 7. Re1 Bg7 8. Nbd2 O-O 9. Nf1 $6 Na5 10. Bb5 a6 11. Ba4 b5 12. Bc2 c5 13. Ng3 Re8 14. d4 $2 {This just opens the position for Black's pieces.} ({Better is the cautious approach} 14. h3 Bb7 15. b4 cxb4 16. cxb4 Nc6 $11) 14... exd4 15. cxd4 Bg4 $1 $17 (15... cxd4 $17 {is also very good for Black.}) 16. d5 (16. dxc5 dxc5 17. e5 Qxd1 18. Rxd1 Nd7 $17) (16. h3 Bxf3 17. Qxf3 cxd4 $17) 16... Nc4 $1 ({After} 16... Bxf3 {, White can reduce the damage with} 17. gxf3 ({But not} 17. Qxf3 Nxd5 18. Bxh6 Bxh6 19. exd5 $17) 17... Nd7 18. Rb1 Nc4 19. b3 Ncb6 20. Be3 $15) 17. Bd3 (17. Rb1 Ne5 18. Bd3 (18. Bf4 Nfd7 {, and White is paralysed.}) 18... Bxf3 19. gxf3 Nxd3 $3 20. Qxd3 c4 21. Qd1 Nd7 22. f4 ({No better is} 22. Be3 Ne5 23. Kg2 Nd3 $17) 22... Nc5 $17) 17... Nd7 $1 18. Rb1 (18. Bxc4 bxc4 19. h3 Bxf3 20. gxf3 Ne5 $17) 18... Nce5 19. Be2 h5 $1 20. Bf4 (20. h3 Nxf3+ $1 (20... Bxf3 21. gxf3 $1) 21. Bxf3 Bxf3 22. Qxf3 (22. gxf3 c4 $1 23. f4 Nc5 $19) 22... Ne5 23. Qd1 c4 $17) (20. Nxe5 Bxe2 21. Qxe2 Nxe5 $17 {Again followed by c5-c4 and Nd3.} 22. f4 $2 {loses after} Ng4 23. Nf1 Bd4+) 20... Bxf3 $1 21. Bxf3 h4 {Avoiding any tricks with Bxh5.} 22. Nf1 c4 $19 23. Bxe5 Nxe5 24. Be2 Nd7 $1 {Rerouting the knight to c5.} 25. Nd2 Nc5 26. b4 $6 {This loses quickly, but other moves do not save White either:} (26. Qc2 Bh6 27. f3 Be3+ 28. Kh1 Qf6 $19) (26. Bf1 Bh6 27. f3 Bf4 $19 {Followed by Qg5.}) 26... Nxe4 27. Nxe4 Rxe4 28. Bf3 Rxe1+ $1 29. Qxe1 Ra7 $1 30. g3 Re7 31. Qd2 Re5 $1 32. Kg2 Qf6 33. Bg4 Re4 34. Bc8 Qe5 35. Bxa6 Re2 36. Qf4 Qxd5+ 37. Kh3 Re4 $1 38. Qc1 Qf5+ 39. Kg2 h3+ 40. Kg1 Re2 0-1

