{White's coffeehouse approach in this game may not be of theoretical importance, but its refutation is highly instructive nonetheless.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d3 h6 5. c3 d6 6. Bb3 g6 7. Nbd2 Bg7 8. Nf1 O-O 9. h3 (9. Ng3 Na5 10. Bc2 c5 11. O-O Re8 ({Also good is} 11... Nc6) 12. d4 $2 exd4 13. cxd4 Bg4 $1 14. d5 b5 15. Rb1 Nc4 $17 {Black has a perfect Benoni position.}) 9... Na5 (9... d5 $1 {is even better:} 10. Ng3 (10. Qe2 $2 {As often in the Italian, this is a bad square for the queen.} a5 $1 11. a4 $17 (11. Ng3 a4 $17) 11... Be6 (11... b6 $1 12. g4 Ba6 13. exd5 Nxd5 $19) 12. Bc2 Nh5 13. Ng3 (13. g4 Nf4 14. Bxf4 exf4 15. e5 d4 $17) 13... Nf4 $1 (13... Nxg3 14. fxg3 f5) 14. Bxf4 (14. Qf1 Re8) 14... exf4 15. Nf1 d4 16. c4 Nb4 $19) 10... Be6 11. O-O dxe4 12. dxe4 Qxd1 13. Rxd1 Bxb3 14. axb3 a5 15. Be3 Rfd8 $15) 10. Bc2 c5 11. g4 $2 {This is just too much optimism.} b5 (11... d5 {looks even better:} 12. Qe2 c4 13. dxc4 dxe4 $17 (13... Nxc4 $5 $17)) 12. Ng3 Bb7 13. Nh4 Nxe4 (13... d5 {is also good:} 14. Qf3 c4 15. dxc4 (15. Nhf5 gxf5 16. Nxf5 cxd3 17. Bxd3 dxe4) 15... Nxc4 16. b3 Nd6 $19) 14. dxe4 Qxh4 $19 15. Be3 Rfd8 16. Qf3 Nc4 17. Bc1 d5 18. b3 Nb6 19. Ba3 Rac8 20. O-O-O d4 21. c4 bxc4 22. bxc4 Nxc4 23. Bb2 Bc6 24. Bb3 Bb5 25. Rhg1 Rc7 26. a4 Ba6 27. Qd3 Nxb2 28. Qxa6 c4 29. Kxb2 Rb8 30. Rb1 Rxb3+ 31. Ka2 Qg5 32. Rxb3 cxb3+ 33. Kxb3 Rc3+ 34. Kb4 Qe7+ 35. Kb5 Qc5# 0-1

