{Mistake 2: Premature h2-h3} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. c3 Nf6 5. d3 a6 6. Nbd2 Ba7 7. O-O d6 8. Bb3 h6 $5 9. h3 $2 (9. Re1 $142 O-O 10. h3) 9... g5 $1 10. Nc4 (10. d4 g4 11. hxg4 Bxg4 $36 (11... Nxg4 $144 $5)) 10... g4 11. hxg4 Bxg4 $5 $15 (11... Nxg4 $144 $5 $15) 12. Ne3 $2 ({Better was} 12. Be3 {, but now Black can increase the pressure on the pin:} Nh7 $1 13. Bxa7 Ng5 $1 14. Ncd2 Nxa7 15. Qe2 Qf6 $17) 12... Bxe3 $3 {A highly counter-intuitive move. Black gives up her important dark-quared bishop to preserve her even more important light-squared one.} 13. Bxe3 (13. fxe3 Qe7 $17 {may have been the lesser evil.}) 13... Rg8 $19 {Black has a decisive kingside attack. It's interesting how active White's bishops look, and yet how little they actually contribute.} 0-1

