1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. c3 Nf6 5. d3 a6 6. a4 d6 7. h3 Ba7 8. O-O $6 O-O $6 (8... h6 $1) 9. Nbd2 ({Lacking development, the immediate} 9. Bg5 $2 {backfires:} h6 10. Bh4 Kh8 $1 $17 {Preparing g7-g5.} 11. Nbd2 {Now Black has a very pleasant choice:} g5 (11... Qe7 {The safe option, calmly preparing g7-g5.} 12. Re1 g5 (12... Rg8 $5) 13. Bg3 (13. Nxg5 $2 hxg5 14. Bxg5 Rg8 $17 15. h4 Rxg5 $1 (15... Rg6 $144 $19) 16. hxg5 Ng4 $19) 13... Rg8 $17 (13... Nh5 $2 14. Nxe5 $1 Nxg3 15. Nxc6 bxc6 16. d4 $1 $16 c5 17. d5 $16) (13... g4 $144 $17)) 12. Bg3 (12. Nxg5 hxg5 13. Bxg5 Rg8 $19 {, for example} 14. h4 Rxg5 $1 15. hxg5 Ng4 16. Nf3 Kg7 17. d4 Qh8 18. g3 Qh3) 12... Nh5 $1 {As a general rule, if White's pawn is still on h2, Black has to play Nh7. Here however, this works, as the g3-bishop is unprotected.} (12... Nh7 13. d4 $5 $132) 13. Bh2 Nf4 14. d4 Qf6 15. dxe5 dxe5 $17) (9. Be3 $6 Bxe3 10. fxe3 Ne7 $1 11. Nbd2 (11. Nh4 d5 $15) 11... Ng6 (11... a5 12. Kh1 Ng6 13. Qc2 c6 $36) 12. a5 (12. Qe2 c6 (12... a5 $5 13. d4 Qe7 14. Rae1 Bd7 15. Bb3 Bc6 16. Bc2 Rae8 $15)) 12... c6 13. b4 d5 $15) 9... Kh8 $5 (9... Be6 $5 10. Bxe6 (10. b4 Bxc4 $5 11. dxc4 $2 (11. Nxc4 d5 $11) 11... Qe7 12. a5 (12. Re1 h6 13. Nf1 Qe6 $15) 12... Qe6 $1 13. Re1 h6 $15) 10... fxe6 11. Re1 (11. Nc4 Qe8 $11 (11... b5 $5)) 11... Nh5 $1 12. Nc4 $4 (12. Nf1 Qe8 (12... Qf6 13. Be3 Nf4 $15) 13. Be3 Nf4 14. Bxa7 Nxa7 $1 15. Ng3 Qg6 16. Re3 c5 $1 17. Kh2 Nc6 $17) 12... Bxf2+ $1 13. Kxf2 Qh4+ 14. Ke2 (14. Kg1 Rxf3 $19) 14... Qg3 15. Rg1 d5 $3 16. Na3 (16. Ncd2 Nf4+ $19) 16... dxe4 17. dxe4 Rad8 18. Qe1 Qg6 $1 19. Bg5 Rd6 $19) (9... h6 $1 10. Re1 Be6 11. Bxe6 fxe6 12. Nc4 Nh5 $1 13. Be3 Qf6 (13... Nf4) 14. Bxa7 Nxa7 15. Ne3 (15. Re3 Nf4) 15... Nf4 16. Kh2 c5 $36 (16... Rf7 $15) (16... Rad8 $3 $36)) 10. b4 Ng8 11. Nb3 $2 (11. b5 $1 Na5 12. Ba2 axb5 13. axb5 Bd7 $132 14. c4 (14. Bc4 Nxc4 15. dxc4 Bxf2+ 16. Rxf2 Rxa1) 14... Ne7) 11... f5 $15 12. b5 Nce7 13. Ng5 Qe8 14. bxa6 bxa6 15. Ne6 Bxe6 16. Bxe6 Qg6 17. exf5 N