1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. O-O Nf6 5. d3 d6 6. c3 a6 7. a4 Ba7 8. Re1 O-O 9. h3 Be6 10. Bxe6 fxe6 11. Be3 Nh5 $5 12. g3 Bxe3 (12... Qf6 $5 13. Nbd2 Qg6 14. Bxa7 Rxa7 15. Nh4 Qf7 16. Qe2 a5 17. Nhf3 h6 $132) 13. Rxe3 Qf6 $132 14. Nbd2 Rf7 $1 (14... a5 $5 {is an interesting alternative, slowing down White's play on the queenside but also giving White some extra time to defend on the kingside.}) 15. b4 Qg6 16. Kh2 Qh6 $5 {This is not possible in the line with 10...h7-h6. Apart from saving a tempo, Black also keeps the option to use the h6-square with his queen.} 17. b5 Ne7 18. Re1 Raf8 $15 19. Qe2 $6 g5 $1 $17 20. Qe3 Ng6 $2 (20... Nf4 21. gxf4 exf4 22. Qe2 g4 23. h4 Kh8 $17 (23... Qh5 $17)) 21. Rg1 Rg7 22. Rg2 Ngf4 23. gxf4 exf4 24. Qd4 e5 25. Qc4+ Kh8 26. Rag1 Rfg8 27. Nxg5 Rxg5 28. Rxg5 Rxg5 29. Rxg5 Qxg5 30. Qxc7 f3 31. Qc8+ Kg7 32. Nxf3 Qf4+ 33. Kg2 Qf7 34. Qg4+ Kf8 35. Ng5 1-0

