1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. c3 Nf6 5. d3 a6 6. O-O d6 7. Bb3 Ba7 8. Nbd2 O-O (8... h6 $5 9. Nc4 g5) 9. h3 h6 10. Re1 Be6 11. Bc2 {If White preserves this bishop, the standard plan for Black is to strike first in the centre in order to obtain a space advantage.} Re8 ({However, with the rook still on f8 it is also possible to insist on kingside play.} 11... Nh7 $5 12. Nf1 (12. b4 $2 Ng5 $15 (12... f5 $144 $15)) 12... Qf6 13. Ng3 (13. Ne3 Rae8 $3 14. b4 Kh8 15. Nd5 Qg6 $36 (15... Qd8 $5 16. a4 f5 $36)) (13. Be3 Bxe3 14. Nxe3 Ng5 15. Nxg5 Qxg5 $132) 13... Ng5 $132) 12. Nf1 d5 $1 13. exd5 Bxd5 (13... Nxd5 $5 14. Nxe5 $2 Nxe5 15. Rxe5 Bxf2+ $17) 14. Ng3 Bc5 $5 (14... Qd6 $5) 15. b4 Bf8 16. a4 g6 17. Ne4 Bg7 18. Be3 Nd7 19. Bb3 Ne7 20. c4 Be6 21. d4 Nf5 22. d5 Nxe3 23. fxe3 Bf5 24. Ng3 e4 25. Nd4 Qg5 26. Ngxf5 gxf5 27. Ra2 f4 28. exf4 Qf6 29. Ne2 a5 30. Ng3 axb4 31. Nxe4 Qd4+ 32. Qxd4 Bxd4+ 33. Kf1 f5 34. Ng3 Nc5 35. Bd1 Rxe1+ 36. Kxe1 b3 37. Bxb3 Nxb3 38. Nxf5 Bg7 39. Re2 Bf8 40. g4 Nc5 41. Kf2 Rxa4 42. Re8 Rxc4 43. Nxh6+ Kg7 44. Nf5+ Kf7 45. Rc8 Ne4+ 46. Ke3 Nd6 47. Nxd6+ Bxd6 48. f5 Rc3+ 49. Ke4 Rxh3 50. g5 Rh4+ 51. Ke3 Rg4 52. g6+ Kf6 0-1

