1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. c3 Nf6 5. d3 a6 6. a4 d6 7. O-O Ba7 8. Re1 O-O 9. h3 h6 10. b4 Be6 (10... Ne7 $1 {This plan gains in strenght here, as White is now less likely to play d3-d4 soon and the knight will sooner or later become a target of a b4-b5 push. A possible line is} 11. Be3 Bxe3 12. Rxe3 Ng6 13. Nbd2 Nf4 $36 (13... c6 $5) 14. Nf1 c6 $1 (14... Kh8 $144 15. Ng3 g5 $36) (14... a5 $5) 15. Ng3 Bxh3 $1 16. gxh3 Nxh3+ 17. Kf1 Ng4 18. Re2 Qf6 19. Rd2 Nhxf2 $19) 11. Bxe6 fxe6 12. Be3 Bxe3 (12... Qe8 $5) 13. Rxe3 Qe8 14. Qb3 Nh5 15. g3 Kh8 16. Nbd2 Rf6 $2 {Overambitious play. Black cuts off the only possible retreat for his knight.} (16... Nf6 $142 17. Kg2 Qf7 $132) (16... Qg6 $142 $5) 17. Rf1 Qf7 18. Nh2 Qg6 19. Ng4 Rf7 20. Kh2 Raf8 21. b5 axb5 22. axb5 Ne7 23. d4 Qg5 (23... Nf4 $5) 24. Rd3 Nxg3 25. Kxg3 h5 26. Qxe6 Ng6 27. Nf3 Qf4+ 28. Kg2 hxg4 29. Qxg6 gxf3+ 30. Kh1 Rf6 31. Qg3 Qxe4 32. Re3 Qf5 33. Kh2 Rg6 34. Rxf3 Rxg3 35. Rxf5 Rxh3+ 36. Kxh3 Rxf5 37. Kg4 Rf4+ 38. Kg5 Rf3 39. dxe5 dxe5 40. Rd1 Kh7 41. c4 Rc3 42. Rh1+ Kg8 43. Rh4 Kf7 44. Kf5 Rf3+ 45. Kxe5 Rxf2 46. Rh8 Re2+ 47. Kd5 g5 48. Rh7+ Kf6 49. Rxc7 g4 50. Rxb7 g3 51. Rb8 g2 52. Rg8 Re5+ 53. Kc6 Rg5 54. Rxg5 Kxg5 55. b6 g1=Q 56. b7 Qh1+ 57. Kb6 Qh2 58. c5 Kf6 59. c6 Ke7 60. Ka7 Qc7 61. Ka8 Qxc6 0-1

