1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. Nc3 {Playing the Italian in the spirit of the Four Knights is a solid and viable option for White, but not very dangerous.} (5. Bg5 $5 {playable but nothing special ...} h6 6. Bh4 d6 7. c3 a6 8. Nbd2 Ba7 {we play some waiting moves..just to see what white wants to do..and then we will castle short most likely!} (8... Qe7) 9. a4 (9. O-O g5 $36 (9... O-O $1 {this is also good..with g5 or Kh8 and g5 to follow soon!} 10. Re1 g5 11. Bg3 Nh7 $1 $132) 10. Bg3 Bg4 $1 {provoking h3}) 9... g5 (9... Qe7 $5 10. b4 g5 11. Bg3 Nh5 $132) 10. Bg3 Nh7 $132) 5... h6 {Stopping any Bg5-ideas that may be unpleasant combined with a white knight on d5.} (5... a6 $5) (5... d6 $5 6. Na4 Bb6 7. Nxb6 axb6 {may be slightly better for White, but it's also fully playable. Black's remaining bishop is a good piece and can halve White's bishop pair with Be6 anytime.}) 6. O-O (6. Nd5 d6 7. c3 a5 8. O-O O-O 9. Be3 Nxd5 10. Bxd5 Bxe3 11. fxe3 Ne7 12. Bb3 Ng6 $11) (6. h3 a6 (6... O-O $2 7. g4 $1 $16 {It's not only White who has to be careful about castling and moving the h-pawn prematurely.}) 7. O-O d6 8. Be3 Bxe3 (8... O-O 9. Bxc5 dxc5 $132) 9. fxe3 Na5 $11) (6. Be3 {Now virtually all bishop moves are fine:} Bxe3 (6... Bb4 $5 7. O-O Bxc3 8. bxc3 d6 $132) (6... Bb6 7. O-O d6 $132) 7. fxe3 d6 8. a4 (8. O-O $6 Na5 $15) 8... O-O 9. O-O Be6 $11) (6. a4 a6 $132 (6... a5 $132)) 6... O-O (6... d6 7. Na4 Bb6) 7. h3 (7. Nd5 d6 8. c3 a5 $1 (8... a6 $5) 9. a4 Kh8 10. Re1 Nxd5 11. Bxd5 Qf6 12. h3 Be6 $11 (12... Bb6 $11)) (7. Be3 Bb6 $1 (7... Bxe3 8. fxe3 d6 $132) 8. Nd5 (8. Bxb6 axb6 9. Nd5 d6 10. a3 Nxd5 11. Bxd5 Ne7 12. Bb3 Ng6 $15 {Now Black can play on the kingside or exchange his bishop on f3 and play for a knight versus isolated Italian bishop position, as seen in the general strategies section.}) 8... d6 9. Nxb6 axb6 10. a4 d5 11. exd5 Nxd5 12. Bd2 Re8 13. Re1 Bg4 $132) 7... a6 $1 8. Be3 d6 (8... Bxe3 $144 9. fxe3 d6 10. a3 Ne7 11. d4 Ng6 $132) 9. Bxc5 dxc5 10. Nd5 (10. Bd5 $6 Nxd5 11. exd5 Nd4 12. Nxe5 Bxh3 $1 13. gxh3 Qg5+ 14. Ng4 f5 15. f4 Qg6 $36) 10... Be6 11. Nxf6+ Qxf6 $11 *

